FADE IN:

[[First scene needs a stronger visual hook]]

EXT. COASTAL HIGHWAY - NIGHT #1#

Rain hammers a lone pickup. HEADLIGHTS carve the dark.

/* cut this beat?
MARA sings along to the radio.
*/

MARA (V.O.)
Everyone said the lighthouse was automated.
Nobody said why it wasn't.

# ACT ONE

= Mara arrives; the keeper is missing.

INT. LIGHTHOUSE - CONTINUOUS #2#

A spiral stair. MARA (30s), soaked, climbs with a flashlight.

MARA
(calling up)
Hello? Mr. Keeler?

The beam sweeps past a coat still dripping on its hook.

MARA (CONT'D)
Great. Terrific.

CUT TO:

.MONTAGE - THE STORM YEARS

> Chyron: "Three winters earlier" <

@KEELER
The sea doesn't forgive, kid.

MARA ^
And still you stayed.

EXT. LIGHTHOUSE - GALLERY - DAWN #3A#

The rain has stopped. Mara leans on the rail.

KEELER (O.S.)
You'll stay too. They always do.

FADE OUT.
